name: gene product is a member of
species specific
description: X speciesSpecific Y means that Y is a general phenomena, like a pathway, and X is the version that appears in a species. X should state which species with RO:0002162 (in taxon)

name: has left-to-right reaction
description: X ltr Y means reaction X of undetermined direction has a left-to-right reaction Y. Relevant for Rhea.

name: has right-to-left reaction
description: X rtl Y means reaction X of undetermined direction has a right-to-left reaction Y. Relevant for Rhea.

name: has bi-directional reaction
description: X bi Y means reaction X of undetermined direction has a bidirectional reaction Y. Relevant for Rhea.

name: is conjugate base of
description: X is conjugate base of Y typically means that X is a deprotonated form of Y

name: is conjugate acid of
description: X is conjugate acid of Y typically means that Y is a protonated form of X

name: is enantiomer of
description: X and Y are in an enantiomeric relationship if flipping all stereocenters of X results in Y

name: is tautomer of
description: X and Y are tautomers if they are different realizations of the resonance structure of the same molecule

name: has parent hydride
description: X has parent hydride Y if the substituents on X are replaced with hydrogens. E.g., SbCl3 has parent hydride SbH3

name: has functional parent
description: X has functional parent Y if X is a derivative (e.g., a salt) of Y. E.g., bepridil hydrochloride has functional parent bepridil

name: is substituent group from
description: connects a group to its chemical entity (e.g., carboyxylic acid group to acetate)

name: has citation
description: connects any entity to a document (e.g., with a pubmed, doi, pmc, or arxiv identifier)
